<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions – QuitDr"
  description="QuitDr Terms and Conditions. Please read these terms before using our telehealth smoking cessation service."
>
  <section class="page-hero" style="padding:3rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p>Please read these terms carefully before using QuitDr.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:2rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <span class="legal-last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</span>

        <p>These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") govern your use of the QuitDr telehealth platform and services ("Service"). By accessing or using QuitDr, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.</p>

        <h2>1. About QuitDr</h2>
        <p>QuitDr is a private telehealth service that connects patients with Australian-registered doctors for smoking cessation consultations, treatment planning, and facilitates medication delivery through partner pharmacies. QuitDr is not a Medicare-registered service.</p>

        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>To use QuitDr, you must:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Be 18 years of age or older</li>
          <li>Be located in Australia at the time of consultation</li>
          <li>Provide accurate and complete health information in the intake form</li>
          <li>Have the legal capacity to enter into a contract</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. The Service</h2>
        <h3>3.1 Telehealth Consultations</h3>
        <p>QuitDr facilitates telehealth consultations between patients and Australian-registered doctors. Consultations are provided for the purpose of smoking cessation assessment and support. The doctor-patient relationship is between you and the treating doctor.</p>

        <h3>3.2 Prescriptions and Medication</h3>
        <p>Prescriptions are issued solely at the clinical discretion of the treating doctor. QuitDr makes no guarantee that a prescription will be issued. Medication is dispensed by an independent licensed pharmacy and delivered to your address.</p>

        <h3>3.3 Not an Emergency Service</h3>
        <p>QuitDr is not an emergency medical service. If you are experiencing a medical emergency, call 000 immediately.</p>

        <h2>4. Fees and Payments</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>$10 Doctor Consultation:</strong> One-time fee, payable at booking.</li>
          <li><strong>$299 3-Month Program:</strong> Full program fee, payable at enrolment.</li>
          <li><strong>Delivery:</strong> $15 flat fee per delivery. Free on orders over $150.</li>
          <li>All fees are in Australian dollars (AUD) and include GST where applicable.</li>
          <li>Payments are processed via Stripe. QuitDr does not store payment card details.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Refund Policy</h2>
        <p>Refunds are considered on a case-by-case basis. As consultations involve the time of Australian-registered medical professionals, fees are generally non-refundable once a consultation has been conducted. If a consultation did not occur due to a QuitDr error, a full refund will be issued. Please contact <a href="mailto:support@quitdr.com.au">support@quitdr.com.au</a> with any refund requests.</p>

        <h2>6. Your Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>You agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate, complete, and up-to-date health information</li>
          <li>Disclose all current medications, allergies, and relevant medical history</li>
          <li>Attend scheduled appointments or provide reasonable notice of cancellation</li>
          <li>Use the platform only for lawful purposes</li>
          <li>Not misuse or attempt to circumvent the platform's security</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Disclaimer of Outcomes</h2>
        <p>QuitDr provides support designed to assist smoking cessation. <strong>We do not guarantee any particular outcome, including quitting smoking.</strong> Treatment effectiveness varies between individuals. The program is designed to support quitting through evidence-based care — outcomes depend on individual factors outside QuitDr's control.</p>

        <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content on the QuitDr platform, including text, design, and software, is owned by or licensed to QuitDr and is protected by Australian intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce or distribute any content without written permission.</p>

        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by Australian Consumer Law, QuitDr's liability for any claim arising from use of the Service is limited to the fees paid by you for the relevant service. QuitDr is not liable for indirect, consequential, or incidental loss.</p>

        <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia. Any disputes are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of New South Wales.</p>

        <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>QuitDr may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the Service after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.</p>

        <h2>12. Contact</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms: <a href="mailto:support@quitdr.com.au">support@quitdr.com.au</a></p>

        <div class="compliance-box" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
          <span class="icon">&#9874;</span>
          <span>QuitDr operates in compliance with the Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA), AHPRA advertising guidelines, and Australian Consumer Law. Results vary between individuals. This is a telehealth service — not covered by Medicare.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
